✅ PART 1: Linux Basics & File Management
🔹 Basic Commands
Bash
Copy code
ls        # list files
cd        # change directory
pwd       # present working directory
mkdir     # create folder
rm -rf    # delete files/folders
cp        # copy files
mv        # move/rename files
touch     # create empty file
cat       # view file
🔹 File Permissions
Bash
Copy code
ls -l
chmod 755 file.sh
chown user:user file.sh
umask
